# Task: Design System Foundation Setup

## Description
Establish the centralized theme infrastructure by creating CSS variables in globals.css and configuring Tailwind theme extension. This creates the single source of truth for all white and red theme colors that will be used across the application.

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] 15 core CSS variables defined in `:root` selector in globals.css
- [ ] Variables include primary colors, text colors, borders, and interactive states
- [ ] Semantic naming convention used (e.g., `--color-accent`, `--color-text-primary`)
- [ ] Tailwind config extended with custom palette mapping to CSS variables
- [ ] Theme tokens accessible via `theme.colors.theme` namespace
- [ ] CSS variable fallbacks work correctly in browsers
- [ ] Documentation added explaining theme variable usage

## Technical Details
**Implementation approach:**
- Define CSS variables in `globals.css` with proper naming
- Primary color: white (#FFFFFF)
- Accent color: red (#DC2626) - verified to meet WCAG AA contrast ratio (4.73:1)
- Configure `tailwind.config.ts` or `tailwind.config.js` to extend theme.colors
- Map Tailwind utilities to CSS variables: `'accent': 'var(--color-accent)'`
- Preserve existing Tailwind color scale for backward compatibility

**Key considerations:**
- Variables must be globally accessible
- Ensure no conflicts with existing styles
- Test variable accessibility in a sample component before proceeding

**Code locations/files affected:**
- `globals.css` (or equivalent global CSS file)
- `tailwind.config.ts` or `tailwind.config.js`

## Dependencies
- [ ] Verify Tailwind CSS is installed and configured
- [ ] Identify correct global CSS file location
- [ ] No blocking dependencies

